Plain glucose (rice) just enters the blood through villi and feeds cells directly,

Pasta always has oils in it. If you hold a lighter to a piece of pasta, it sweats oil becoming greasy.
Pasta burns way more intensely than rice (wheat germ oil).
Its Nutrition Facts table even states that pasta contains fat.
Breads are oily (oils are used in all doughs).
Potato has alkaloids like those in foxglove, despite having no oil(s) like rice.
Rice is the only fat free starch that has no phytochemicals such as solanine.
